title: Rocket Lab establishes new U.S. foothold with successful launch after years of delays
summary: Rocket Lab’s first U.S. launch got off the ground Tuesday evening, marking a successful mission and a long-awaited expansion of the company’s capabilities.

title: Spaceflight books dedicated Isar Aerospace launch in 2026
summary: U.S.-based launch services provider Spaceflight said Jan. 25 it has booked a dedicated launch in 2026 from Isar Aerospace, the German rocket developer aiming to perform the first test flight of its Spectrum vehicle this year.

title: Astrobotic completes Peregrine testing
summary: Astrobotic Technologies said that it has completed testing of its Peregrine lunar lander and it ready to ship it to Cape Canaveral for launch.

title: Rocket Lab conducts first Electron launch from American soil
summary: Rocket Lab, which has operated its Electron small-satellite launcher successfully from New Zealand since 2017, as now inaugurated its first US-based launch site. After weather and paperwork-related delays, the mission named “Virginia Is For Launch Lovers” lifted off at the opening of a two-hour window at 6:00 PM EST (23:00 UTC) on Tuesday, Jan. 24.

title: Space Command: U.S. satellites ‘constrained’ by lack of mobility
summary: Lt. Gen. Shaw said a key concern is that U.S. surveillance satellites that monitor potentially hostile activities are at disadvantage because of their limited maneuverability

title: Space Force not buying large satellites for the foreseeable future
summary: The era of massive satellites needs to be in the rear view mirror for the Department of Defense, the head of military space acquisitions Frank Calvelli said Jan. 24.

title: NASA and DARPA to partner on nuclear thermal propulsion demonstration
summary: NASA and DARPA will cooperate on the development and flight demonstration of a nuclear propulsion system with applications for both national security and space exploration.

title: Buckle up, it could get bumpy: The space economy’s vaunted resilience will be tested in 2023
summary: While challenging economic conditions this year will hit some space companies harder than others, the industry as a whole is expected to remain robust as multiple headwinds rock the sector.
